message.content:
A cucumber is a long, cylindrical, and green vegetable/fruit that belongs to the gourd family. 
It is known for its high water content and refreshing taste. 
The skin of a cucumber is usually smooth and waxy with small bumps or ridges. 
The texture of the cucumber is firm and crunchy when raw, but becomes softer when cooked. 
Cucumbers are often used in salads, sandwiches, and as a garnish. 
They can be found in grocery stores and farmers markets worldwide typically from spring to late summer. 
Cucumbers are also often pickled for use in sandwiches, soups and stews.
